T1  - Preplay Communication, Participation Restrictions, and Efficiency in Initial Public Offerings
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/4.4.709
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 4
IS  - 4
SP  - 709
EP  - 726
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The extent to which the observed procedures for selling new issues are efficient is studied. We show that a posted-price mechanism, in conjunction with nonbinding preplay communication and participation restrictions, leads to an allocation of the security (and payment) that maximizes the seller’s expected revenue, given the informational constraints imposed by the optimizing incentives of the potential buyers.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/4.4.709
ER  - 



